'''Elisabeth R. Finch''' (sometimes credited as '''Elisabeth Finch''') is an American [[television writer]], best known for her work on the [[HBO]] vampire series ''[[True Blood]]''. She often works on projects with her writing partner [[Kate Barnow]].
== Early career == Finch began her career by writing a [[short film]] entitled ''Looking for My Brother''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0842013/|title=Looking for My Brother (2006)|work=IMDb|accessdate=September 3, 2010}}</ref> She, along with Barnow, were then hired as writer's assistants on ''True Blood'' for the second season. Her first writing credit for that show came with the tenth episode of that season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2353156/|title=Elisabeth Finch|work=IMDb|accessdate=September 3, 2010}}</ref>
