{{use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox person |image = | name = Ewa Petelska | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1920|12|24|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Pyzdry]], [[Wielkopolskie]], [[Second Polish Republic|Poland]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2013|08|20|1920|12|24|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]] | occupation = Film director, screenwriter | yearsactive = 1951–1990 }}
'''Ewa Petelska''' (24 December 1920 &ndash; 20 August 2013) was a Polish [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,75475,14467717,Zmarla_Ewa_Petelska__wybitna_rezyserka_filmow_wojennych.html |title=Zmarła Ewa Petelska, wybitna reżyserka filmów wojennych i historycznych |language=pl |publisher=Wyborcza.pl |date= |accessdate=2013-08-21}}</ref><ref name="filmpolski">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmpolski.pl/fp/index.php/112935 |title=Ewa Petelska |accessdate=2011-12-10 |work=filmpolski}}</ref> She directed 26 films between 1951 and 1985. Her 1963 film ''[[Black Wings (film)|Black Wings]]'' (''Czarne skrzydła'') was entered into the [[3rd Moscow International Film Festival]] where it won a Silver Prize.<ref name="Moscow1963">{{cite web |url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff36/eng/archives/?year=1963 |title=3rd Moscow International Film Festival (1963) |accessdate=2012-12-01 |work=MIFF}}</ref> Her 1973 film ''[[Copernicus (film)|Copernicus]]'' (''Kopernik'') was entered into the [[8th Moscow International Film Festival]] where it won the Silver Prize.<ref name="Moscow1973">{{cite web |url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff36/eng/archives/?year=1973 |title=8th Moscow International Film Festival (1973) |accessdate=2013-01-03 |work=MIFF}}</ref>
She often collaborated with her husband, [[Czesław Petelski]].
==Selected filmography== * ''[[Ogniomistrz Kaleń]]'' (1961) * ''[[Black Wings (film)|Black Wings]]'' (1963) * ''[[Tortura nadziei]]'' (1967) * ''[[Kwestia sumienia]]'' (1967) * ''[[Copernicus (film)|Copernicus]]'' (1973) * ''[[Kazimierz Wielki (film)|Kazimierz Wielki]]'' (1976)
