{{italic title}}
'''''Formula Comitis Archiatrorum''''' is the earliest known code of [[medical ethics]].<ref name="Nemec">{{cite book |url=https://www.nlm.nih.gov/hmd/pdf/highlights.pdf |title=Highlights in Medicolegal Relations |first=Jaroslav |last=Nemec |publisher=National Library of Medicine}}</ref> It was written in the 5th century,<ref name="Nemec" /> during the reign of the [[Ostrogoths|Ostrogothic]] king [[Theodoric the Great|Theodoric]], and is preserved in the works of [[Cassiodorus]]. It demands from physicians that they widen and deepen their knowledge and enacts the consultation with other physicians.

